text: Pseudogyrinocheilus prochilus is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae, found in Yangtze River and its tributaries in China. This species is the only member of its genus.Zheng, L.-P., Chen, X.-Y. & Yang, J.-X. (2016): Molecular systematics of the Labeonini inhabiting the karst regions in southwest China (Teleostei, Cypriniformes).
